  "response": "That's a complex philosophical and psychological question. Different perspectives exist:\n\n1. Some argue romantic love is a genuine form of love, involving deep emotional connection and commitment.\n\n2. Others view it as a temporary emotional state or biological mechanism for reproduction.\n\n3. Many psychological theories suggest romantic love is a combination of emotional, chemical, and social factors.\n\n4. Different cultures and individuals have varied interpretations of what constitutes \"real\" love.\n\nUltimately, there's no universally agreed-upon definition, and perspectives can differ based on personal, cultural, and philosophical beliefs.",
